          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Different</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Premium square layout</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Different</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tile point values</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Different</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Word dictionaries</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Board Layout Differences</h2>

      <p>The most impactful difference is where premium squares are positioned. This fundamentally changes opening strategy, scoring potential, and defensive considerations.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎯 Scrabble Board</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Triple word scores in corners and midpoints of edges. Double words form a diamond pattern. Center star is a double-word square. Layout creates clear hot zones and dead zones that skilled players exploit.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📱 Words With Friends Board</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Premium squares repositioned throughout the board with a different pattern. Triple word squares are not in corners. The layout creates more accessible scoring opportunities but less dramatic swings between great and poor positions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Strategic Impact of Board Design</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Scrabble's board creates <span class="text-white font-medium">higher variance between turns</span> — a perfectly-placed word can score 100+ while a blocked board yields only 15-20. Words With Friends' layout distributes scoring more evenly, making individual mega-turns less common but consistent scoring more achievable.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Tile Values and Distribution</h2>

      <p>Several letters have different point values between the two games. This affects which words are power plays in each system.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Higher in WWF:</span> J is worth 10 (vs 8 in Scrabble), H is worth 4 (vs 4), and several other tiles differ by 1-2 points. These small differences compound over a full game.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Tile distribution:</span> Both games use 100 tiles but with slightly different letter frequencies. Scrabble has 12 E tiles; WWF has 13. These differences subtly affect probability calculations and rack composition strategies.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Blank tiles:</span> Both games have 2 blanks worth 0 points. Their strategic importance is identical in both games — the most valuable tiles for bingo creation regardless of which platform you play on.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Dictionary and Competitive Differences</h2>

      <p>The dictionary difference is arguably the most confusing aspect for players who switch between games. A word valid in one may be rejected in the other.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Scrabble Ecosystem</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Official dictionaries (TWL, Collins/SOWPODS). Active tournament circuit worldwide. Official ratings. Physical board game available. 75+ years of competitive tradition and community.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Words With Friends Ecosystem</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Proprietary dictionary (the Enable word list with modifications). Mobile-first design. Social gaming features. No official tournament structure. Massive casual player base. Regular updates and events.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Which Should You Play?</h2>

      <p>Both games develop word skills and strategic thinking. Your choice depends on what you value most in a word game experience.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Choose Scrabble if:</span> You want competitive depth, tournament opportunities, official ratings, physical board game options, and a game with 75+ years of strategic development and community.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Choose Words With Friends if:</span> You prioritise mobile convenience, social features, casual play with friends, and a large matchmaking pool. The lower barrier to entry makes it easier to find opponents quickly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play both if:</span> Skills transfer well between games. Word knowledge, pattern recognition, and strategic thinking apply to both. Just be aware of dictionary differences to avoid confusion about which words are valid where.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

